					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13284232#post-4673194</guid>
				<title>RULES UPDATE TEN: RESTRICTIONS ON EDITING CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13284232/exquisite-corpse-contest#post-4673194</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2020 21:55:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>A Random Day</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1841781</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>For Phase 2, You may edit the Containment Procedures you receive beyond image localization. However, their original intent and meaning must remain identifiable if shown to the original author. The submitter of the Containment Procedures should still receive coauthor credit. Contest runners will look at entries upon request to determine the extent of each author’s contribution and how much a coauthor’s contribution <em>needed</em> to be edited.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
