					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13284232#post-4646918</guid>
				<title>RULES UPDATE EIGHT: SCP NUMBERING</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13284232/exquisite-corpse-contest#post-4646918</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2020 18:34:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>A Random Day</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1841781</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>For Phase 1, do not add an SCP number to your containment procedures submission. Use some variation of &quot;SCP-XXXX&quot; or &quot;SCP-#&quot; or some other placeholder.</p> <p>For Phase 2, in addition to submitting your entry as a regular or -EX SCP (object class permitting), you may submit it as a -J article or an 001 Proposal.</p> 
				 	]]>
